# Cursor Configuration Management

## Canonical Source

- **Repository**: `~/saski/augmentedcode-configuration`
- **GitHub**: `github.com/saski/augmentedcode-configuration`
- **Global Config**: `~/.cursor/rules/` and `~/.cursor/commands/`

This repository is the single source of truth for all Cursor IDE configuration.

## Bidirectional Sync Workflow

### When editing global config (~/.cursor/)
After modifying files in `~/.cursor/rules/` or `~/.cursor/commands/`:
1. Run `./sync-cursor-config.sh global-to-repo` from the repository directory
2. Commit and push to GitHub

### When editing the repository
After modifying files in `~/saski/augmentedcode-configuration/.cursor/`:
1. Run `./sync-cursor-config.sh repo-to-global` from the repository directory
2. Restart Cursor if needed

### Automated Sync Script

Use the provided sync script for easy bidirectional synchronization:

```bash
# From repository directory
cd ~/saski/augmentedcode-configuration
./sync-cursor-config.sh [repo-to-global|global-to-repo|both]
```

**Default behavior**: Running without arguments syncs both directions.

### Manual Sync Commands

If you prefer manual sync:

```bash
# Repo to Global
cp -r ~/saski/augmentedcode-configuration/.cursor/rules/* ~/.cursor/rules/
cp -r ~/saski/augmentedcode-configuration/.cursor/commands/* ~/.cursor/commands/

# Global to Repo
cp -r ~/.cursor/rules/* ~/saski/augmentedcode-configuration/.cursor/rules/
cp -r ~/.cursor/commands/* ~/saski/augmentedcode-configuration/.cursor/commands/
```

## Reminder

Always keep both locations synchronized. The GitHub repository serves as backup and version control.
